message.content:
cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.SY

The paper discusses instantaneously trained neural networks (ITNNs) and their applications in artificial intelligence (AI). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper describes various versions of the corner-classification family of ITNNs, which have applications in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The implementation issues discussed in the paper also suggest that it could belong to the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category.
